   Good candidates for memoization in a typical codebase:

• Pure functions with deterministic output that are called repeatedly with the same arguments
  - Mathematical formulas (e.g., factorial, power calculations)
  - String transformations (e.g., slug generation, case conversions)
  - Parsing results (e.g., JSON/YAML parsing, regex matches)

• Expensive operations whose inputs do not change between calls
  - Database queries with same parameters
  - API calls with identical request parameters
  - Heavy computations (e.g., matrix multiplications, sorting algorithms)

• Recursive functions where sub-problem results are reused
  - Dynamic programming algorithms (e.g., Fibonacci, knapsack problem)
  - Tree/graph traversal with overlapping subproblems

• Rendering or layout calculations in UI code
  - Component render functions with immutable props/state
  - CSS calculations that depend on viewport dimensions
  - Chart/graphics rendering with static data

Key requirement: The function must be pure (no side effects) and return deterministic results for the same input.


